{"id":14881338,"mediaExerciseId":"b62229df-a984-43cb-b839-93d1c1f046ec","exerciseName":"2","chapterName":"12","chapterTitle":"Some Lessons From Capital Market History","groupId":612362,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":414,"solutions":[{"id":6128419,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"Just like the previous question, some investors were able to undertake higher risk since they are expecting higher rewards. Holding the stock can only result in two things: losing more money if the stock goes down, or making more profit if the stock rises. Since the stock is already in the negative, the investors predicted and expected that it will get back to positive returns soon that is why they held the stock. Since they are expecting big rewards, they went and undertook the big risk which unfortunately did not play out in their favor. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"dc7c840b-2710-4ace-8c6e-37e80462901a","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":1}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881339,"exerciseName":"3","page":414,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"5655cd15-0bfd-4576-b540-15ad18cea47d